description: Yonsei University Museum, located in Seoul, South Korea, is a very famous local museum. There are many ancient ceramic works in the museum, which is a good place for tourists to learn about the history of Korea. In addition, there is also a library here.

description: Wudu Mountain Unified Observatory is located in Paju City, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea. It was built at an altitude of 118 meters on Wudu Mountain near the Han River and Imjin River. Here, you can see the scenery of Kaesong Songyue Mountain and Seoul 63 Building. If you use a telescope If so, you can see the North Korean propaganda village.

In this exhibition, the artist continued the "Weather Series", using materials to replace the time represented by the weather, transferring the temperature and humidity of the four seasons collected during the second chapter of the residency in 2023 to the canvas and presenting it.
